 I add a Java test that writes a class file as a resource? I'm wondering if I could create a Gradle task to copy a class from a dependency into the test resources. But it looks like the user wants to keep tests in Java under src/test/java. I’m not sure if adding that resource would be a shadow issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering version management**\\n\\nI realize I shouldn't hardcode versions in a version-agnostic context—it's just bad practice. An alternative might be to create a Java class in the test package, compile it, and embed the resource config. But I can't change the path for getResourceAsStream; it’s fixed. I could use build.gradle to dynamically copy from a dependency jar. It’s getting complicated, so I might want to switch to lower-level classes like `LocationManager` or `JavaModuleDescriptor`. I want to ensure coverage isn’t lost with dynamic access reporting too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating module access**\\n\\nI'm wondering if I can use the public API `JavaModuleDescriptor`, which indirectly utilizes `MainClass`. But it seems like the error only references `MainClass` specifically, and I might need to read beyond that for context. It could be helpful to inspect the test report to really understand the dynamic access situation. However, it seems like dynamic access might not even be necessary. I should also look for a test in version 1.0.0 to compare results.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XlkikPP9BOlNhjrcU0OWyoKM|fc_0f187344f9955547016a26a1e5c820819081ba7f2d88cb558a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-java/1.0.0/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_java/MainClassModuleNameExtractorTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 815, "output": 1063, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30038, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780916679560, "responseId": "resp_0f187344f9955547016a26a1c8070881908d93cf8a3b472466"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_XlkikPP9BOlNhjrcU0OWyoKM|fc_0f187344f9955547016a26a1e5c820819081ba7f2d88cb558a", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_codehaus_plexus.plexus_java;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.jar.Attributes;\nimport java.util.jar.JarEntry;\nimport java.util.jar.JarOutputStream;\nimport java.util.jar.Manifest;\nimport org.codehaus.plexus.languages.java.jpms.MainClassModuleNameExtractor;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\npublic class MainClassModuleNameExtractorTest {\n    private static final String MODULE_NAME = \"org.example.plexus.fixture\";\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path temporaryDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void getsAutomaticModuleNameFromJarManifest() throws Exception {\n        Path moduleJar = createAutomaticModuleJar();\n        MainClassModuleNameExtractor extractor =\n                new MainClassModuleNameExtractor(Path.of(System.getProperty(\"java.home\")));\n\n        Map<Path, String> moduleNames = extractor.extract(Map.of(moduleJar, moduleJar));\n\n        assertThat(moduleNames).containsEntry(moduleJar, MODULE_NAME);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void extractsModuleNamesThroughForkedMainClass() throws Exception {\n        Path moduleJar = createAutomaticModuleJar();\n        MainClassModuleNameExtractor extractor =\n                new MainClassModuleNameExtractor(Path.of(System.getProperty(\"java.home\")));\n\n        Map<String, String> moduleNames = extractor.extract(Map.of(\"fixture\", moduleJar));\n\n        assertThat(moduleNames).containsEntry(\"fixture\", MODULE_NAME);\n    }\n\n    private Path createAutomaticModuleJar() throws IOException {\n        Path moduleJar = Files.createTempFile(temporaryDirectory, \"automatic-module\", \".jar\");\n        Manifest manifest = new Manifest();\n        Attributes attributes = manifest.getMainAttributes();\n        attributes.put(Attributes.Name.MANIFEST_VERSION, \"1.0\");\n        attributes.putValue(\"Automatic-Module-Name\", MODULE_NAME);\n\n        try (OutputStream outputStream = Files.newOutputStream(moduleJar);\n                JarOutputStream jarOutputStream = new JarOutputStream(outputStream, manifest)) {\n            JarEntry resourceEntry = new JarEntry(\"org/example/plexus/fixture/resource.txt\");\n            jarOutputStream.putNextEntry(resourceEntry);\n            jarOutputStream.write(\"fixture\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n            jarOutputStream.closeEntry();\n        }\n        return moduleJar;\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780916710078}]}
